
## FULL OUTER JOIN Explanation

A **FULL OUTER JOIN** returns **all rows from BOTH tables**, combining the results of both LEFT OUTER JOIN and RIGHT OUTER JOIN.

### Visual Representation

```
LEFT TABLE (employee)          RIGHT TABLE (department)
┌──────────────┐              ┌──────────────┐
│ Aarav        │              │ IT Dept      │
│ Maya         │              │ DB Dept      │
│ Liam (NULL)  │──────JOIN──── │ Infra Dept   │
│ Rajesh (NULL)│              │ R&D Dept (NULL)
└──────────────┘              └──────────────┘

FULL OUTER JOIN = All from LEFT + All from RIGHT
```

### Syntax

```sql
SELECT e.first_name, d.department_ID, d.department_name
FROM employee e
FULL OUTER JOIN department d
USING (employee_id);
```

