### Key Differences

| Join Type | Shows | Example |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| **INNER JOIN** | Only matching rows | 9 rows (only matched pairs) |
| **LEFT OUTER JOIN** | All from left + matching right | 11 rows (all employees, some with NULL departments) |
| **RIGHT OUTER JOIN** | All from right + matching left | 10 rows (all departments, some with NULL employees) |
| **FULL OUTER JOIN** | All from both tables | 12 rows (all employees + all departments) |

### FULL OUTER JOIN with Your Data

```sql
SELECT COALESCE(e.first_name, 'NO EMPLOYEE') as Employee_Name,
       d.department_ID, 
       d.department_name
FROM employee e
FULL OUTER JOIN department d
USING (employee_id);
```

